---
Every event dict from EventDetector must contain exactly:
  city (str), event_type (str), timestamp (datetime),
  summary (str), reason (str), metrics (dict)

Allowed event_type values (no others):
  sudden_temp_drop, sudden_temp_rise, city_anomaly, feels_like_gap,
  dangerous_wind, wind_shift, heavy_precipitation, precip_streak,
  weather_code_severity

- summary: one human-readable sentence, no technical jargon
- reason: explains WHY it fired — must include threshold and actual value
- metrics: must contain the numeric values that triggered the event

Correct example:
{
  "city": "Ottawa",
  "event_type": "feels_like_gap",
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T14:00:00",
  "summary": "Ottawa feels 11 degrees colder than the actual temperature.",
  "reason": "Apparent temp (-6C) deviates 11C from actual (5C), exceeding 8C threshold.",
  "metrics": {"temperature": 5.0, "apparent_temperature": -6.0, "gap": 11.0}
}
